        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 9 at 7:29PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 729 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles north of Groom, or 16 miles east of Panhandle, moving east at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Groom and Lake Mcclellan.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
